{
"id":"faq005",
"question":"How do I delete unwanted items?",
"answer":"DELETE A PHOTJOURNAL ENTRY \r\rGo to the PhotoJournal tab and tap the list icon in the top right. Find the item you want to delete, and swipe left.  \r\rDELETE AN ACTION \r\rGo to the Actions tab and tap the list icon in the top right. Go to either the Past Action or My Custom Action Ideas Page, find the item you want to delete, and swipe left. NOTE: Each active action is a unique copy of the original action idea, which you can alter. If you want to delete the active copy as well, tap on the action to get into its detail page, tap Edit in the top right, change the status to Done, and tap Done in the top right. Now you will find the action in the Past Actions, and you can delete it from there.  \r\rDELETE A PERSON OR POD\r\rYou first need to archive them as inactive. Active persons or pods are protected from deletion.   \r\rFor a PERSON, tap on the person's face to get to the person's detail view.    \r\rTap Edit.   \r\rScroll to the bottom and check 'Archive Person as Inactive'.  \r\rGo to the People Tab and tap the list icon in the top left.   \r\rFind the person you want to delete and swipe left.  \r\rTo delete a POD, do the same as a person, but go to the pod's detail view instead of the person to find 'Archive This Square As Inactive.'\r\rNOTE: If you delete a pod or person, you will lose your entire history with them. We recommend you only delete persons or pods that are 'junk' or were entered in error. You don't need to delete an inactive person or pod if you might meet with them later. Inactive persons and pods are hidden so they won't clutter up your views.",
