"id":"faq011",
"question":"What do you do if someone doesn't sense God is speaking to them or suggesting an action to take?",
"answer":"It’s true that the Listen moment may not result in any specific prompts from God. In that case, look at the action options and see what appeals to you by style, and just pick one. You can’t force God to speak to you in any given moment. But you can choose to try something that can help you explore or grow in that area, and notice what happens between you and God as a result. \r\rIn addition, if later it seems like God is prompting something more specific to do related to that topic, you can always change what your action step was. The goal is primarily to follow the Spirit and share what God is doing in your life. Sticking to the action you originally chose during the convo would be secondary. \r\rIn the God Connect moment, no one is required to share anything after that, only those who have something they want to share need to share anything at that point. If nothing discernible happens for some people, no problem. It’s fine if sometimes it's just a moment to take a deep breath, relax, and focus on God for a quiet moment. \r\rWe’re not trying to force anything, we’re just creating space to listen.",
